The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and data representation, which are central topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on multi-agent systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of representation learning and dynamic alignment methods suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the discovery of structure in data, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
